#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""Panel tray indicator for Claude Linux<->Mac sync health.

Badge colors: green = healthy & mirrored, amber = Mac away or transfer
running, red = a local service is down.

Left-click toggles a popup status card (single instance; closes when you
click anywhere outside it). Right-click for the menu.

COSMIC notes: tray creation is gated on org.kde.StatusNotifierWatcher and
recreated if the watcher's owner changes (panel restart) — Qt caches tray
availability at first call, so creating too early breaks autostart. The app
runs on xcb (XWayland) so the popup can be positioned near the cursor and
take focus; the tray itself is D-Bus (SNI) and doesn't care.
"""
